---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "build a project — ecute.club";
---
<BaseLayout {title}>
  <article class="container">
    <h1>build a project</h1>
    <p>pick an idea, sketch the circuit, prototype on a breadboard, then solder it neatly. here’s a gentle path + tiny starter projects.</p>

    <div class="diagram" role="img" aria-label="flow: idea → breadboard → solder → case">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 760 120" width="100%" height="auto">
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="760" height="120" rx="16" fill="var(--card)"/>
        <!-- steps -->
        <g transform="translate(40,24)">
          <rect width="150" height="72" rx="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="75" y="44" text-anchor="middle" class="mono">idea ✏️</text>
        </g>
        <g transform="translate(230,24)">
          <rect width="150" height="72" rx="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="75" y="28" text-anchor="middle" class="mono">breadboard</text>
          <text x="75" y="48" text-anchor="middle" class="mono mini">try parts</text>
        </g>
        <g transform="translate(420,24)">
          <rect width="150" height="72" rx="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="75" y="28" text-anchor="middle" class="mono">solder</text>
          <text x="75" y="48" text-anchor="middle" class="mono mini">make it solid</text>
        </g>
        <g transform="translate(610,24)">
          <rect width="150" height="72" rx="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="75" y="28" text-anchor="middle" class="mono">enclose</text>
          <text x="75" y="48" text-anchor="middle" class="mono mini">case / mount</text>
        </g>
        <!-- arrows -->
        <line x1="190" y1="60" x2="230" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"/>
        <polygon points="230,60 222,55 222,65" fill="currentColor"/>
        <line x1="380" y1="60" x2="420" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"/>
        <polygon points="420,60 412,55 412,65" fill="currentColor"/>
        <line x1="570" y1="60" x2="610" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"/>
        <polygon points="610,60 602,55 602,65" fill="currentColor"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="callout ok">
      start here: <a href="/guides/breadboard">breadboard</a> →
      <a href="/guides/leds">leds</a> →
      <a href="/guides/resistors">resistors</a> →
      <a href="/guides/soldering">soldering</a>.
    </div>

    <h2>tiny starter projects</h2>
    <h3>1) 555 blink (no code)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>uses <a href="/guides/555">555 timer</a> in astable mode.</li>
      <li>parts: NE555, R1 1 kΩ, R2 10 kΩ, C 10 µF, LED, 330 Ω, 5 V.</li>
      <li>freq: <code>f = 1 / (0.693 × (R1 + 2R2) × C)</code> (≈6.5 Hz with values above).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2) button → led (microcontroller)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>any Arduino/ESP32 board, 1× button, 10 kΩ pull-up/pull-down, 1× LED + 330 Ω.</li>
      <li>learn: inputs, debouncing (<a href="/guides/switches">switches</a>), PWM dimming.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3) touch lamp (MOSFET)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>logic-level N-MOSFET (e.g., AO3400), LED strip, 12 V, 100 kΩ gate pulldown, 100 Ω in series with gate.</li>
      <li>learn: low-side switching &amp; current paths (<a href="/guides/transistors">transistors</a>).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>tools you’ll actually use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>soldering iron + brass wool/sponge, leaded 63/37 solder, flux pen</li>
      <li>side cutters, tweezers, small pliers</li>
      <li>digital multimeter (DMM)</li>
      <li>hookup wire + jumper kit</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>neatness checklist</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>short leads, parts aligned, labels on rails</li>
      <li>decouple each IC: <strong>0.1 µF</strong> at the pins, plus bulk on the rail</li>
      <li>no strain on cables; use proper connectors</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout info">
      next step: turn the breadboard into a PCB — see <a href="/guides/pcb">pcb basics</a>.
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
